    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but like, when looking at the actual data, isn't there a more factual side? like, the studies on crime reduction seem more like hard evidence, whereas the constitutional arguments are just based on how people interpret the law. wouldn't you say the statistical approach is more \"correct\" in a scientific sense?",
